just_use WireAction.elm

# label: WORKHORSE (wire-action-v2)
# role: domain — action-shaped wire format for the LynRummy port

Action-shaped wire format. Each `WireAction` value names what
the player did (split, merge-stack, merge-hand, place-hand,
move-stack, draw, discard, complete-turn, undo); receiver
derives post-state by applying the action to prior state. No
diff on the wire.

Replaces the TS diff-based format (`stacks_to_remove` +
`stacks_to_add` + inferred trick). See
`showell/claude_writings/actions_not_diffs.md` for the
rationale.

## Exposed surface

- `type WireAction` — 9 constructors
- `encode : WireAction -> Json.Encode.Value`
- `decoder : Json.Decode.Decoder WireAction`

## JSON shape (wire contract)

```
{"action":"split","stack_index":I,"card_index":I}
{"action":"merge_stack","source_stack":I,"target_stack":I,"side":S}
{"action":"merge_hand","hand_card":C,"target_stack":I,"side":S}
{"action":"place_hand","hand_card":C,"loc":L}
{"action":"move_stack","stack_index":I,"new_loc":L}
{"action":"draw"}
{"action":"discard","hand_card":C}
{"action":"complete_turn"}
{"action":"undo"}
```

Where `S = "left" | "right"`, `C = encoded Card`, `L = {top, left}`.

Stacks are referenced by **positional index** in the board
list (V1 choice). Hand cards are referenced by **content
identity** (Card, not HandCard — wire doesn't carry state).

## Tests

`tests/LynRummy/WireActionTest.elm`:
- Round-trip (encode → decode → equal) for every constructor.
- Exact-JSON format tests for 4 representative shapes
  (split / merge_stack / complete_turn / draw) to lock the
  wire contract against accidental drift.
- 4 decode-error tests (unknown tag, missing payload, bad
  side value, missing action tag).

## Pointers

- Consumer: will be `Main.elm` (outbound on player actions)
  and the Go server (inbound validation + persist). Neither
  wired up yet.
- Go counterpart: pending. Will mirror this shape via tagged
  JSON; cross-language conformance tests live near
  `games/lynrummy/conformance/` when written.
- Depends on: `LynRummy.Card.encodeCard` / `cardDecoder`,
  `LynRummy.CardStack.encodeBoardLocation` /
  `boardLocationDecoder`, `LynRummy.BoardActions.Side`.
